<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123H21/6: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-15T21:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">April 15,
                                        1919, 9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    April 16, 5.50 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1626. The President has made the following recess appointments as
                            Ministers: … Hugh Gibson to Poland … Gibson has accepted.<note n="1" xml:id="d732fn1">His commission was issued Apr. 16.</note></p>
                        <pb facs="0827" n="742" xml:id="pg_742"/>
                        <p>I took the liberty of asking Paderewski if Gibson would be acceptable and
                            he said that he would. …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed>Lansing</signed><lb/><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>